    "title": "Principal Plant Manager at SAIL International Enterprises",
    "description": "Join the SAIL International Enterprises family as a Plant Manager in Pimpri-Chinchwad. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout SAIL International Enterprises:\nSAIL International Enterprises is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in 5S\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Learning & development budget\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pimpri-Chinchwad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with SAIL International Enterprises!",
